## [FAIL] HIGH Рђћ A4b: `GRID_MAX_HEIGHT_COVER` not guarded by `isFirst` Рєњ pure image-slides regress

**What the spec says:** A4b replaces `<ImageGrid maxHeight={GRID_MAX_HEIGHT} />` in "the grid-kind branch" with `maxHeight={GRID_MAX_HEIGHT_COVER}` (500). The code snippet in A4b shows no `isFirst` guard.

**What a developer will implement:** They will replace the `<ImageGrid>` call in the entire `kind === "grid"` branch. Non-first grid slides (pure image slides, Slides 2..N) will also receive `maxHeight={GRID_MAX_HEIGHT_COVER = 500}` instead of the existing `GRID_MAX_HEIGHT = 700`.

**Why it breaks:** A1c explicitly states: "Existing `GRID_MAX_HEIGHT = 700` bleibt unmodifiziert f├╝r image-only-Slides (Slides 2..N im image-mode haben kein Title/Lead/Hashtags)." The two specs are contradictory because A4b's code snippet doesn't show an `isFirst` condition. Pure image slides will silently render 28% shorter.

**Fix required:** A4b must say: "In the `kind === 'grid' && isFirst === true` (cover-grid) sub-branch, replaceРђд" and show the full conditional. The non-isFirst branch retains `GRID_MAX_HEIGHT` and the original `slide.gridColumns`/`slide.gridImages` props.

