## [FAIL] MEDIUM Рђћ A3e: `lead-empty-grid-cover` edge-case test referenced but absent from E2

**What the spec says in A3e:** "Im no-grid-cover-Branch ist Lead bei leadOnSlide===true per Definition non-empty Рђћ falls nicht, m├╝sste der Renderer das selbst checken; siehe E2 lead-empty-edge-case-Test."

**What E2 contains:** No such test. The E2 list covers lead-on-grid (`slides[0].kind === "grid"` carries lead), `leadOnSlide === false` for grid-path text-slides, no-grid Slide-0 `leadOnSlide: true`, and the budget test. No lead-empty test appears.

**What a developer will implement:** They will implement the listed E2 tests and miss the edge case. The JSX conditional `{meta.lead && <LeadBlock ...>}` in the grid-cover branch is correct but untested. Codex will note the gap between A3e's reference and E2's coverage.

**Fix required:** Add to E2: "grid-path with `lead === null/empty`: `slides[0].kind === "grid"`, verify no LeadBlock rendered on cover (LeadBlock conditional guard, A3e)."

