## [FAIL] MEDIUM Рђћ A3b/buildManualSlides: two partial rules, no combined expression Рєњ wrong implementation likely

**What the spec says:**
- A2 / Files-to-Change item (a): "`buildManualSlides` hardcodet `leadOnSlide: false` f├╝r text-slides bei grid-path REGARDLESS of stored value."
- A3b / Files-to-Change item (c): "idx===0 setzt explizit `leadOnSlide: !hasGrid`."

**What a developer will implement (two failure modes):**
- Implementing only A2 (false for all): `leadOnSlide: false` for all slides in the forEach. No-grid Slide-0 never gets `leadOnSlide: true` Рєњ the `isFirst && leadOnSlide === true` detection condition in SlideTemplate never fires Рєњ no-grid Slide-1 renders without centered Title+Lead (entire A3 visual change silently missing).
- Implementing only A3b without idx guard: `leadOnSlide: !hasGrid` for ALL forEach slides Рєњ all no-grid continuation slides get `leadOnSlide: true` Рєњ Lead renders on every no-grid text slide.

**Why the spec is ambiguous:** No single code snippet shows the combined expression. A3b's NACHHER code block says "(f├╝r idx === 0): `leadOnSlide: !hasGrid`" Рђћ the idx condition is only in a comment, not the code body. The forEach loop snippet earlier in A3b shows only the grid-path fix (`leadOnSlide: false`), not the no-grid Slide-0 fix. A developer reading linearly may implement one but miss the other.

**Fix required:** Add a single synthesizing code block:
```ts
// buildManualSlides Рђћ forEach over override.slides:
override.slides.forEach((overrideSlide, idx) => {
  // ...
  rawSlides.push({
    kind: "text",
    blocks: slideBlocks,
    leadOnSlide: !hasGrid && idx === 0,  // true ONLY for no-grid Slide-0; false everywhere else
  });
});
```

