**What the spec says:** A5/A5d add a new `imageCount` state and modify its initialization. No mention of auditing `useCallback`/`useMemo` dep-lists in `InstagramExportModal.tsx`.

**What lessons.md documents:** "PR #110 Codex R1 [P2]: `handleDownload = useCallback(Рђд)` liest `imageCount` im body aber hat's nicht in deps Рєњ stale-closure." This was a real Codex finding in the same file, same hook, added when `imageCount` was first introduced.

**What a developer will implement:** They will not re-audit dep-lists because the spec doesn't ask them to. If `handleDownload` (or any other callback) was subsequently re-organized and `imageCount` was ever dropped from its deps, re-introducing the default-init logic in A5d could expose the same stale-closure bug. Codex will flag it if found.

**Fix required:** Add to A5d or Code-Quality Gates: "Audit all `useCallback`/`useMemo` in `InstagramExportModal.tsx` that read `imageCount`; confirm `imageCount` is in their dep-lists (PR #110 Codex P2 precedent)."

